                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                                        <placeName>Montreal</placeName>\n                                        <date>16<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> April /49</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                                        <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">\n                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Dear Friend—</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(5)\">Last week I intended adding<lb/> some news items\n                                        to the letter I there sent you, but being<lb/> interrupted,\n                                        was obliged to close my letter ,as <add>מועד</add> was\n                                        close<lb/> at hand. I shall now send you some news, though\n                                        not<lb/> all I then intended, as I received the\n                                                  <date>March</date> &amp; <date>April</date> nos\n                                        of<lb/> the Occident just as I was going to Synagogue on the\n                                        day<lb/> I had been abusing your agent (and justly so I\n                                        guess) for<lb/> delay. I see you noticed the appointment of\n                                                  <persName>Mr Benjamin</persName> &amp;<lb/> the\n                                        examination of our S. S. you or rather <persName>Dr\n                                                  D</persName> gives me<lb/> credit however for\n                                        something more than my due. If the<lb/> young ones “got up”\n                                        their Purim play in a surprising<lb/> manner to them\n                                        entirely, and not to me, be the credit.<lb/> They and their\n                                        parents were the sole agents, I certainly<lb/> indulged them\n                                        with <hi rend=\"underline\">3</hi> rehearsals, and encouraged\n                                        them to<lb/> get on with their design, firstly because these\n                                        kind of<lb/> things are the grounds for those future\n                                        reminiscences of<lb/> pleasant boy hood, which cause us to\n                                        love the feasts<lb/> of the Almighty because they are the\n                                        feasts of our youth, and<lb/> secondly because it was\n                                        improving to them. The notes on<lb/> Perisol<add>?</add>\n                                        have been very correctly inserted this time, true<lb/> there\n                                        are a few other graphical errors, but what of them?<lb/> It\n                                        strikes me that I shall be rather hard pushed to send<lb/>\n                                        you the continuation as I have so many things to do and<lb/>\n                                        in a very short time. <persName>Dr Wise</persName> is rather\n                                        severe but not unjustly</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3nc5sv7p/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
