                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3nc5sv7p/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>so, on our singing <add>חזנים</add> and <sic>accomodating</sic>\n                                        placemen, From<lb/> the circulars received I find that you\n                                        are not desirous that<lb/> our congregation should have\n                                        anything to do with the proposed<lb/> assembly. True you\n                                        send us circulars, but these circulars<lb/> tell us that the\n                                        delegates are only to be from congregations<lb/> in the\n                                        Union. We Britishers are to be kept out, whether<lb/> near\n                                        as <placeName>Canada</placeName> or distant as the\n                                                  <placeName>West Indies</placeName>. I think<lb/> I\n                                        may say, however, that the majority of my congregation<lb/>\n                                        approve the measure. I might it is true call a meeting<lb/>\n                                        the result of which would undoubtedly be a resolution<lb/>\n                                        unanimously passed after this fashion “Resolved. That\n                                        as<lb/> we are not wanted in the proposed assembly; as\n                                        is<lb/> evident from a circular just received from\n                                                  <persName>Rev I Leeser</persName>,<lb/> we will\n                                        not <add>?</add> ourselves where we may not be<lb/> welcome.\n                                        But this I wish to avoid, now my dear friend<lb/> if you\n                                        really desire to see this congregation represented<lb/> at\n                                        the ensuing meeting, just take notice of what<lb/> I have\n                                        written above and give me answer <add>פתחו לי השער</add></p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">For English news I have to inform you that\n                                        the<lb/> cheap Jewish Library is being forwarded with, i. e\n                                        the<lb/> next no of the Evenings in Judea is being now put\n                                        to<lb/> press. It was with the most deep regret that I\n                                        heard<lb/> of the death of <persName>Hananel de Castro\n                                                  Esqr.</persName>, a most<lb/> excellent member of\n                                        our community in <placeName>England</placeName>. I was\n                                        on<lb/> excellent terms with him and corresponded with\n                                        him.<lb/> He might be truly said to be the picture of\n                                        health? <add>אדם להכל דתה</add><lb/>\n                                        <add>מה אנוש</add> The loss of <persName>DeCastro</persName>\n                                        is a national loss.<lb/> His death was sudden, having been\n                                        seized with a fit</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3nc5sv7p/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
